        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <h3 class="title subsection-title">Proof Machine</h3>
            <div class="content">
            <p class="muted">LTO Network’s Proof Machine allows you to secure any digital data against manipulation, protecting businesses against digital fraud.</p>
            <p class="muted">Our Proof Machine is easy to integrate into existing IT infrastructures and connect to any (legacy) system through an API.</p>
            <p class="muted">Add a layer of trust to invoices, medical records, emails, documents and other digital data in a matter of minutes at a fraction of the costs.</p>
            </div>
          <a class="read-more-link "href="#" >
            <p class="read-more deep-lavender"><br>Read more →</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="columns has-margin-top-40 inverted-mobile">
        <div class="column">
          <h3 class="title subsection-title">Workflow Machine</h3>
            <div class="content">
          <p class="muted">Data silos are the top barrier for organizations to reach the next level of efficiency when doing business together. This is hard to solve as stakeholders are reluctant to create and manage shared systems that allow for automation and effective collaboration.</p>
                <p class="muted">LTO Network has created a tamper-proof system that lets organizations create trustless, automated workflows to operate on equal footing through so-called "Live Contracts".</p>
            </div>
          <a class="read-more-link "href="#" >
            <p class="read-more deep-lavender"><br>Read more →</p>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="icon-container column" style="left:48px;width:280px;height:250px;background-image: url('/assets/rocks/rock-1.svg')">
          <img style="position:absolute;width:26px;top:90px;left:-40px" src="/assets/small-rock-2.svg">
          <img style="position:absolute;width:70px;top:20px;left:-20px" src="/assets/small-rock-1.svg">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="columns has-margin-top-40">
        <div class="icon-container column" style="left:48px;width:280px;height:250px;background-image: url('/assets/rocks/rock-1.svg')">
          <img style="position:absolute;width:26px;top:90px;left:-40px" src="/assets/small-rock-2.svg">
          <img style="position:absolute;width:70px;top:20px;left:-20px" src="/assets/small-rock-1.svg">
        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <h3 class="title subsection-title">Data Sharing <small>(Linked data)</small></h3>
            <div class="content">
          <p class="muted">When information is sent via email, letters, etc it becomes hard to keep track of which data is shared with whom and for what reason. This makes it nearly impossible to comply with privacy legislation like GDPR..</p>
            <p class="muted">The LTO Network private layer allows systems across organizations to share data in a compliant way.</p>
            </div>
          <a class="read-more-link "href="#" >
            <p class="read-more deep-lavender"><br>Read more →</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<div class="section-container cutout-bottom-alt">
  <section class="section alt p-top-l neg-m-top-m">
    <div class="section-body">
      <div class="container">
          <div class="columns is-vcentered">
                <div class="column is-one-third">
                <h2 class="section-title">Why LTO Network</h2>
                    <div class="content">
                    <p class="muted">We came up with a different approach than most other enterprise fabrics. We created a complex layer to execute business logic in miniature private chains. These are created following our Live Contracts protocol.</p>
                    <p class="muted">Every process becomes a self-contained mini-blockchain and data and business logic is only shared between the participants on that single chain. We combined this with our  lightweight public chain with the sole purpose of anchoring data.</p>
                    <p class="muted">This brings advantages such as horizontal scalability, the possibility to delete data from the mini-chains and setting up a node in a matter of minutes instead of days.</p>
                    </div>
                    <a href="#" class="button is-rounded is-primary main-button use-cases">Learn more</a>
                </div>
                <div class="column is-two-third">
                    <img src="/assets/why-lto.svg">
                </div>
            </div>
      </div>
